Petavision may be obtained from sourceforge.net using the subversion command into the Terminal:

    svn co https://petavision.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/petavision/trunk petavision
    
You should also check out one of the example projects, for example:

    svn co https://petavision.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/petavision/examples/CellularAutomata ca
    
If you want to use a branch (for example, the hyperstructure branch):

    svn co https://petavision.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/petavision/branches/hyperstructure petavision
    
To build petavision without Eclipse:
   1. change to the root project directory (using the "cd" command)
   2. Type "make" (this will make src/pv_example and src/build/libpv.a)

To run petavision without Eclipse:
   1. "cd" to the root project directory
   2. Type "src/pv_example -n 2 -p input/inparams.txt -i input/const_one_64x64.tif"
   
To run one of the examples (using make to build):
   1. First make the PetaVision library (see above)
   2. "cd" to the example directory that you want to build
   3. Type "make"
   4. Type "pv_ca -n 500 -p input/params.pv -i input/one-pixel.tif"
    